-- Unicredit's Bulgaria business gains 50 mln euro credit line
-- By Angel Krasimirov
-- Fri Mar 21, 2014 07:47AM EDT
-- None



SOFIA, March 21 (Reuters) - Unicredit Bulbank, Bulgaria's largest bank by assets, has secured a 50 million euro ($68.92 million) credit line from the European Investment Bank <EIB.UL>, it said on Friday.

The financing is part of a 100 million euro loan to be disbursed in two tranches and used to extend loans to small and medium-size enterprises operating in agriculture, industry and services, the Unicredit <CRDI.MI> subsidiary said.